{
  "message": "chore(conformance): regenerate reports after DNS/f128 nativization\n\nUpdate conformance artifacts to reflect the 12 symbols promoted from\nGlibcCallThrough to Implemented (DNS resolver family + f128 parse\ninternals). Key metric changes:\n\n- total_exported: 2774 -> 2776\n- implemented: 1580 -> 2104 (57% -> 76%)\n- glibc_call_through: 810 -> 288 (29% -> 10%)\n\nFiles updated:\n- support_matrix.json: __res_mkquery, __res_nclose, __res_ninit,\n  __res_nmkquery, __res_nquery, __res_nquerydomain, __res_nsearch,\n  __res_nsend, __res_querydomain, __res_send, __strtof128_internal,\n  __wcstof128_internal all now show \"Implemented\" status.\n- reality_report.v1.json: refreshed implementation counts.\n- support_matrix_maintenance_report.v1.json: refreshed drift report.\n- conformance/lib.rs: add #[allow(clippy::needless_return)] matching\n  the same fix applied in harness diff.rs.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
